.SH NAME
svc_rdma_encode_reply_chunk \- Encode RPC Reply's Reply chunk
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" svc_rdma_encode_reply_chunk
.BI "(struct svc_rdma_recv_ctxt *rctxt "  ","
.BI "struct svc_rdma_send_ctxt *sctxt "  ","
.BI "unsigned int length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rctxt" 12
Reply context with information about the RPC Call
.IP "sctxt" 12
Send context for the RPC Reply
.IP "length" 12
size in bytes of the payload in the Reply chunk
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return values:
On success, returns length in bytes of the Reply XDR buffer
that was consumed by the Reply's Reply chunk
-EMSGSIZE on XDR buffer overflow
-E2BIG if the RPC message is larger than the Reply chunk
